<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxy38812ac03cfb4f2ba06c302e810ef43e-5">Faith services</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="not-answered">Prayer area <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">On-site chapel <span>(not answered)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContentd49433babfb0439fa09b91524660e8c9">
</div>
<p>The Chaplaincy department across the Trust seeks to make spiritual care available to all . A Team made up of dedicated staff and volunteers is available on each site to provide :•	a listening ear•	a presence in times of distress, anxiety, or grief•	help in the spiritual search to understand illness and one’s situation•	support on ethical and religious questions•	help in clarifying where one is in lifeFor particular religious needs, the chaplaincy service will provide prayer and sacraments within the Christian tradition and endeavour to resource faith traditions not represented within the team. There is a chapel on each site in the hospital. These are</p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
